{Speech 6 Answer 49}{}{And how are things with you, Dusty?\n}
{Speech 7}{}{What can I do for you?}
{Speech 7 Answer Exit}{}{Goo-goo!}
{Speech 7 Answer Barter}{}{You pour! Me drink!}
{Speech 7 Answer 40}{}{Work! [Pound your chest with a fierce look] Caps! Eat! Work!}
{Speech 7 Answer 44}{}{[Wink at Dusty] Hey! Caps for me!}
{Speech 20}{}{[He waved his hand] Ah... What's it to you...}
{Speech 20 Answer 21}{}{Maybe I can help?}
{Speech 21}{}{Hmm, maybe... So here's the thing, @sex@|buddy|girl|. Those crooks from the government are planning to throw some kind of "reception" here. I'm not against it, of course. There's just one "but"...}
{Speech 21 Answer 22}{}{Go on.}
{Speech 22}{}{The thing is, I'm having some trouble with my booze supply right now. No, not the ordinary swill, there's always plenty of that. But Rot Gut and Gamma are running low.}
{Speech 22 Answer 23}{}{You want me to help you deliver the booze? Who's your supplier?}
{Speech 22 Answer Exit}{}{Drinking is bad for your health. Let them wash down their canapes with water. So long, Dusty [Leave] }
{Speech 23}{}{It's not that simple, @pname@. If I had a reliable supplier, I'd have gone to him long ago.}
{Speech 23 Answer 24}{}{So where am I supposed to get this hooch?}
{Speech 24}{}{I don't know... Maybe ask around town... I need a crate each of Gamma and Rot Gut. But I'll pay you for every bottle!}
{Speech 24 Answer 25}{}{It's a deal! I'll help you save face.}
{Speech 24 Answer Exit}{}{You know, Dusty, I don't have time to go searching for booze. [Leave]}
{Speech 25}{}{Thanks! You're a lifesaver!}
{Speech 26}{}{Well, did you manage to find anything?}
{Speech 26 Answer Exit}{}{I'm working on it, but I've got nothing to make you happy yet.}
{Speech 26 Answer 27}{}{Yes, I've got a bottle of Rot Gut!}
{Speech 26 Answer 29}{}{Yes, I've got a bottle of Rot Gut.}
{Speech 26 Answer 28}{}{Yes, I've got a bottle of Gamma Gulp beer.}
{Speech 26 Answer 30}{}{Yes, I've got a bottle of Gamma Gulp beer.}
{Speech 27}{}{Excellent! I pay 50 coins for every bottle of Rot Gut. Good price. Anything else?}
{Speech 28}{}{Excellent! I pay 30 coins for every bottle of Gamma beer. Good price. Anything else?}
{Speech 29}{}{No, thanks, I've collected all the Rot Gut I need. But Gamma I could still use.}
{Speech 30}{}{No, thanks, I've collected all the Gamma. It's Rot Gut I'm short on}
{Speech 31}{}{That's it, buddy, thanks for your help! Now I've got plenty of booze!}
{Speech 31 Answer 48}{}{Yeah, you really had me running all over town!}
{Speech 40}{}{Glad to see you, my brainless friend. I've got work for you. As long as you promise not to eat it all yourself on the way, of course.}
{Speech 40 Answer 41}{}{Work! [Shake your head wildly] No eat me work! You pay caps?}
{Speech 41}{}{[The bartender looks at you with obvious doubt and mutters to himself] No eat me work. Hmm. Where to put the comma... Oh well. Let's risk it. \nI'll pay you 2 [holds up 1 finger] coins if you carry food to the sheriff. And remember. The sheriff needs food, not bones and trash like last time. Got it?}
{Speech 41 Answer 42}{}{[Make a clever face]Rrggacharrggr!! 2 - too few caps. HUNDRED [Hold up 3 fingers] - many caps!}
{Speech 41 Answer Exit}{}{Cheat! Pull wool over eyes. No fool me! [Leave]}
{Speech 42}{}{A hundred? For a hundred coins I'll go to the sheriff myself. 5 coins is all I can offer [Holds up 2 fingers] You'll get the money when you come back from the sheriff.}
{Speech 42 Answer Exit}{}{5 caps too few! Need respect! [Spit and leave]}
{Speech 42 Answer 43}{}{5 caps! Give food. Carry sheriff fast. Take caps fast-fast.}
{Speech 43}{}{Well, it's settled then. Mind you don't lose the food along the way. }
{Speech 44}{}{[The bartender looks very closely into your eyes] Did you carry the food to the sheriff? Everything all right? Didn't lose anything? Sure?}
{Speech 44 Answer 45}{}{Sheriff angry! No want eat! Curse!}
{Speech 44 Answer 47}{}{[Make an offended face] Carry fast. You talk for nothing. Sheriff full!}
{Speech 44 Answer 46}{}{[Spread your hands] Sheriff full. Me eat! Tasty! Give more!}
{Speech 45}{}{I don't know anything. Go to the sheriff again. Try to make him like you. [Laughs loudly]}
{Speech 46}{}{Ate it all yourself?? What a glutton. Why did I ever trust you. I ought to charge you for that meal, but to hell with it. Get out of my sight!}
{Speech 47}{}{Good job! Here's your honestly earned reward. Just keep in mind. If I find out you cheated me@sex@|| - you'll regret it.}
{Speech 48}{}{Yes, I really appreciate your help, @sex@|buddy|girl|!\n}
{Speech 48 Answer Exit}{}{See you around. [Leave]}
{Speech 49}{}{Not bad, not bad. Want a drink?}
{Speech 49 Answer Exit}{}{Thanks, I'm not in the mood to drink. See you around. [Leave]}
{Speech 49 Answer 50}{}{Pour it! Keep the change![Put 200 coins on the counter]}
{Speech 50}{}{[He whistles and takes the money] What's got "us" so generous today? [Holds out a glass]}
{Speech 50 Answer Exit}{}{Even I@sex@|| don't get it. [Down it in one and leave]}
{Speech 50 Answer 51}{}{Nothing special. Just in a good mood. Any news?}
{Speech 51}{}{Nothing special. It's relatively quiet around here. Not like it used to be, phew!}
{Speech 51 Answer 52}{}{So it was lively before, was it?}
{Speech 52}{}{Well, um, all sorts of things happened. Take that story about the murder of the president's son, for example.}
{Speech 52 Answer 53}{}{What nonsense? I've seen his son. He hangs out with the ragers, a little punk.}
{Speech 53}{}{Who did you see@sex@||?!? Ah... I'm not talking about Carlson right now. I mean Tandi. She used to be president...}
{Speech 53 Answer 54}{}{Uh-huh, I've heard@sex@||. But didn't she die a long time ago?}
{Speech 54}{}{Yep. And do you know why?}
{Speech 54 Answer 55}{}{They say it was old age. She was nearly a hundred years old.}
{Speech 55}{}{That played a part too, of course. But on the whole, Tandi's health was surprisingly fine. It was when the Chosen One killed her son, Hoss, that she started failing right away.}
{Speech 55 Answer Exit}{}{All right, I'm not interested in this for now. [Leave]}
{Speech 55 Answer 56}{}{What? The Chosen One? I've heard@sex@|| of him. He killed the President's son? How did it happen?}
{Speech 56}{}{I saw it all with my own eyes. }
{Speech 56 Answer 57}{}{Will you tell me?}
{Speech 57}{}{Hoss was a pretty nasty type, nothing like his mother. He was always hanging around my bar.}
{Speech 57 Answer 58}{}{Drinking?}
{Speech 58}{}{Yeah, he drank a lot. Whenever he got drunk, he'd start picking fights with the customers. And it often came to blows. The police turned a blind eye to his antics, no surprise there. After all, Hoss was Tandi's son!}
{Speech 58 Answer Exit}{}{All right, I'd better go. [Leave]}
{Speech 58 Answer 59}{}{And one day he crossed the Chosen One?}
{Speech 59}{}{Yeah, something like that. The Chosen One dropped by to wet his whistle. Well, everyone knew him here, and a lot of folks came running to get a look at the living legend.}
{Speech 59 Answer 60}{}{Get to the point, Dusty.}
{Speech 60}{}{Hoss, as always, was sitting at the bar, blind drunk. When he saw the Chosen One, he swaggered up to him and let loose a few crude jokes.}
{Speech 60 Answer 61}{}{And what did the Chosen One do?}
{Speech 61}{}{The Chosen One scornfully tossed off some remark and turned away from Tandi's son. I don't know what he said, but Hoss just went berserk. He grabbed a chair and smashed it over the Chosen One's back.}
{Speech 61 Answer 62}{}{I wonder what he said to him... Then what?}
{Speech 62}{}{And then it was all over... The Chosen One turned around, calm as could be, as if no one had even touched him, and planted one right on Hoss's jaw. Tandi's son flew into the wall and never got back up... Later they said he got a brain hemorrhage and died on the spot.}
{Speech 62 Answer 63}{}{Wow!}
{Speech 63}{}{Crazy stuff, isn't it? And Hoss usually sat right at this very table... Right next to you, in fact...}
{Speech 63 Answer Exit}{}{Horrible. All right, I'd better go, see you. [Leave]}
{Speech 65}{}{Easy, what do you want to know?}
{Speech 65 Answer 66}{}{Have you seen anyone suspicious around lately?}
{Speech 66}{}{Suspicious who? What do you mean?}
{Speech 66 Answer 67}{}{For example, monstrous oversized ants devouring virgins in the city streets...}
{Speech 66 Answer 68}{}{New people in town, strangers, something like that.}
{Speech 67}{}{Whoa! Haven't seen any, hold on, I'll go take a look...}
{Speech 68}{}{Yeah, somebody shows up regularly.}
{Speech 68 Answer 69}{}{For example? }
{Speech 69}{}{Yeah, there are crowds of them hanging around here. They all look alike, but there are differences too.}
{Speech 69 Answer 70}{}{Alike how? Are they bandits? }
{Speech 70}{}{Some kind of savages in blue suits with numbers on the back... Oh. You've got a little suit like that too?}
{Speech 70 Answer Exit}{}{Never mind, take care, Dusty. [Leave]}
{Speech 200}{}{Who are you interested in?..@@Give me a name...@@Who are you looking for?..}
{Speech 200 Answer Exit}{}{I'd better go.}
{Speech 200 Answer 201}{}{Where can I find this person?}
{Speech 201}{}{That information costs money... for three hundred I'll tell you what I know.}
{Speech 201 Answer Exit}{}{I'd better go.}
{Speech 201 Answer 202}{}{It's a deal, here's the money.}
{Speech 202}{}{So, who are you interested in?..@@Remind me of the name...@@Who are you looking for?..}
{Speech 202 Answer Exit}{}{Well, I'll be off...}
{100000001}{}{Now you know what happened to Tandi's son.}
